name: language_sql_data_curly_apostrophe_name
description: |
  U+2019 RIGHT SINGLE QUOTATION MARK resembles an ASCII apostrophe but is not an
  SQL quote delimiter. Smart-quote conversion or normalization performed after
  validation can turn safe data into syntax-significant data.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: utf8
unicode-meta:
  code-units: 10
  code-points: 8
  scalar-values: 8
  legacy-grapheme-clusters: 8
  extended-grapheme-clusters: 8
tags:
  - "language"
  - "sql"
  - "sql-data"
  - "utf8"
  - "apostrophe"
  - "smart-quote"
  - "normalization"
  - "text-spoofing"
---
O’Reilly
